<subSubSection id="F2FEBCA29A77FFFC3589F893A58EF81C" pageId="7" pageNumber="224" type="description">
<paragraph id="BA5BEF299A77FFFC3589F893A58EF81C" blockId="7.[151,1436,1905,2040]" pageId="7" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis id="8890333B9A77FFFC3589F893A782F86F" bold="true" box="[151,214,1905,1931]" pageId="7" pageNumber="224">Note.</emphasis>
Re-examination of the 
<typeStatus id="655F518B9A77FFFC34FEF890A544F868" box="[480,528,1906,1932]" pageId="7" pageNumber="224">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="7DE494AA9A77FFFC37ADF893A4C5F86F" baseAuthorityName="Devyatkin" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[691,913,1905,1931]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similissima">
<emphasis id="8890333B9A77FFFC37ADF893A4C5F86F" box="[691,913,1905,1931]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="224">Pedesta similissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="22DFF3AC9A77FFFC36BFF893A4A7F86F" box="[929,1011,1905,1931]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1842,1867]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,982,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,982,1817]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 26. Holotype of Pedesta similissima syn. n. a. adult, dorsal side. b. ditto, ventral side. c. label. d. ring and left valva, lateral view. e. tegumen and uncus, dorsal view. f. right valva, outer side. g. aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3687845" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3687845/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="224">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="22DFF3AC9A77FFFC311EF893A305F86F" box="[1024,1105,1905,1931]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1759,1784]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,535,1728]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1435,525,1734]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 27. Male genitalia of a paratype [V3] of Pedesta similissima syn. n. a. genital capsule, right side. b. ditto, left side. c. ditto, dorsal view. d. ditto, ventral view. e. gnathos and uncus, ventral view. f. tegumen, oblique dorsal view. g. right valva, inner side. h. ditto, dorsal view. i. ditto, outer side. j. left valva, inner side. k. ditto, dorsal view. l. ditto, outer side. m. aedeagus, lateral view. n. ditto, dorsal view. p. juxta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3687847" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3687847/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="224">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) shows that both the external and genitalic characters are identical to those of 
<taxonomicName id="7DE494AA9A77FFFC37A8F874A41FF84B" baseAuthorityName="Leech" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[694,843,1941,1967]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submacula">
<emphasis id="8890333B9A77FFFC37A8F874A41FF84B" box="[694,843,1941,1967]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="224">P. submacula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="22DFF3AC9A77FFFC3645F877A481F84B" box="[859,981,1941,1967]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1837,1862]" captionTargetBox="[153,1428,459,1806]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,453,1812]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3–17. Adults of Pedesta rubella stat. n. and P. submaucla. 3–8. P. rubella, from Nonggang NNR of Guangxi. 3–7. male; 8. female. 9–17. P. submaucla. 9, 14. male, from Shaanxi; 10. male, from Chongqing; 11. female, from Chongqing; 12. male, from Guizhou; 13, 15. female, from Guizhou; 16. male, from Guangdong; 17. female, from Guangdong. Scale bar = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3687827" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3687827/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="224">Figs. 9–17</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="22DFF3AC9A77FFFC36FFF877A367F84B" box="[993,1075,1941,1967]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1812,1837]" captionTargetBox="[163,1422,859,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,848,1787]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 18. Male genitalia of Pedesta submacula from Chongqing. a. ring, lateral view. b. uncus and gnathos, dorsal view. c. ditto, ventral view. d. right valva, inner side. e. ditto, dorsal view. f. ditto, outer side. g. left valva, inner side. h. ditto, dorsal view. i. ditto, outer side. l. aedeagus, left lateral view. m. ditto, right lateral view. k. ditto, dorsal view. n. juxta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3687829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3687829/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="224">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
), suggesting the two species are conspecific. The analysis of COI gene sequences confirmed this point (
<figureCitation id="22DFF3AC9A77FFFC36B2F85BA4B9F837" box="[940,1005,1977,2003]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1967,1992]" captionTargetBox="[210,1373,714,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[197,1390,705,1941]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. NJ tree based on Kimura-2-Parameter distances for partial mitochondrial COI sequences from 28 individuals of Pedesta, values at nodes represent the bootstrap support (BP) values." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3687823" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3687823/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="224">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="DE7592D89A77FFFC311BF85BA39EF837" author="Devyatkin, A. L." box="[1029,1226,1977,2003]" pageId="7" pageNumber="224" pagination="127 - 135" refId="ref5768" refString="Devyatkin, A. L. (2002) Hesperiidae of Vietnam, 11. New taxa of the subfamily Hesperiinae (Lepidoptera, Hesperiidae). Atalanta, 33 (1 / 2), 127 - 135." type="journal article" year="2002">Devyatkin (2002)</bibRefCitation>
mistook 
<taxonomicName id="7DE494AA9A77FFFC302FF858A2C8F837" baseAuthorityName="Devyatkin" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[1329,1436,1977,2003]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubella">
<emphasis id="8890333B9A77FFFC302FF858A2C8F837" box="[1329,1436,1977,2003]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="224">P. rubella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName id="7DE494AA9A77FFFC35A1F83CA607F813" baseAuthorityName="Leech" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[191,339,2013,2039]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submacula">
<emphasis id="8890333B9A77FFFC35A1F83CA607F813" box="[191,339,2013,2039]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="224">P. submacula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and thus resulted in this synonym.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="EE9BBFA19A78FFF33589FC7DA571FC38" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3687833" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3687833" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3687833/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="225" startId="8.[151,250,927,952]" targetBox="[174,1413,196,897]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph id="BA5BEF299A78FFF33589FC7DA571FC38" blockId="8.[151,1437,927,988]" pageId="8" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="8890333B9A78FFF33589FC7DA64DFC5C" bold="true" box="[151,281,927,952]" pageId="8" pageNumber="225">FIGURE 20</emphasis>
. Male genital capsule of 
<taxonomicName id="7DE494AA9A78FFF33709FC42A5E2FC5C" baseAuthorityName="Devyatkin" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[535,694,928,952]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubella">
