<subSubSection id="F2FEBCA29A79FFF735D9F9C0A604FE37" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="229" pageId="9" pageNumber="226" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="BA5BEF299A79FFF235D9F9C0A26CF8F0" blockId="9.[151,1437,1570,1957]" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis id="8890333B9A79FFF235D9F9C0A635F9D9" bold="true" box="[199,353,1570,1597]" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">Distribution.</emphasis>
Based upon the specimens examined, data from literature (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="DE7592D89A79FFF2312FF9C0A3A7F9D9" author="Ikeda, K. &amp; Nishimura, M. &amp; Inagaki, H." box="[1073,1267,1570,1597]" pageId="9" pageNumber="226" pagination="58 - 66" refId="ref6101" refString="Ikeda, K., Nishimura, M. &amp; Inagaki, H. (2001) Butterflies of Cuc Phuong National Park in northern Vietnam (5). Butterflies, 30, 58 - 66." type="journal article" year="2001">
Ikeda 
<emphasis id="8890333B9A79FFF23169F9C1A3FDF9D8" box="[1143,1193,1570,1596]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">et al</emphasis>
. 2001
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="DE7592D89A79FFF231E1F9C1A787F985" author="Wang, M. &amp; Tang, D. M." pageId="9" pageNumber="226" refId="ref6572" refString="Wang, M. &amp; Tang, D. M. (2012) Butterflies of Guangxi Maoershan National Nature Reserve. Guangxi Nationalities Publishing House, Nanning, 194 pp." type="book" year="2012">Wang &amp; Tang 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="DE7592D89A79FFF235C0F9A4A608F984" author="Chen, Z. J." box="[222,348,1606,1632]" pageId="9" pageNumber="226" refId="ref5703" refString="Chen, Z. J. (2016) Guizhou Butterfly. Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang, 557 pp." type="book" year="2016">Chen 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="DE7592D89A79FFF23478F9A4A547F985" author="Zhu, L. X. &amp; Liu, Z. H. &amp; Yu, L. &amp; Ou, Y. Y." box="[358,531,1606,1633]" pageId="9" pageNumber="226" refId="ref6672" refString="Zhu, L. X., Liu, Z. H., Yu, L. &amp; Ou, Y. Y. (2017) Butterfly Fauna of Anhui. Press of University of Science and Technology of China, Hefei, 429 pp." type="book" year="2017">
Zhu 
<emphasis id="8890333B9A79FFF23484F9A5A69FF984" box="[410,459,1606,1632]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
) and results of the present study, a distribution map of 
<taxonomicName id="7DE494AA9A79FFF23167F9A4A205F984" baseAuthorityName="Leech" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[1145,1361,1606,1632]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submacula">
<emphasis id="8890333B9A79FFF23167F9A4A205F984" box="[1145,1361,1606,1632]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">Pedesta submacula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7DE494AA9A79FFF23096F9A5A7BCF960" baseAuthorityName="Devyatkin" baseAuthorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubella">
<emphasis id="8890333B9A79FFF23096F9A5A7BCF960" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">P. rubella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is provided (
<figureCitation id="22DFF3AC9A79FFF23467F988A698F961" box="[377,460,1642,1669]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1893,1918]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1868]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1435,181,1868]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 28. Distribution map of Pedesta submacula and P. rubella stat. n." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3687849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3687849/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). It shows that 
<taxonomicName id="7DE494AA9A79FFF2376CF989A451F960" baseAuthorityName="Leech" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[626,773,1642,1668]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submacula">
<emphasis id="8890333B9A79FFF2376CF989A451F960" box="[626,773,1642,1668]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">P. submacula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed from northwestern Qinling Mountains through the southern mainland 
<collectingCountry id="C2F3AFB99A79FFF234E5F96CA56AF94C" box="[507,574,1678,1704]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">China</collectingCountry>
to central 
<collectingCountry id="C2F3AFB99A79FFF237A7F96CA44FF94C" box="[697,795,1678,1704]" name="Vietnam" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, but in southern Guangxi and northern 
<collectingCountry id="C2F3AFB99A79FFF231C2F96CA26AF94C" box="[1244,1342,1678,1704]" name="Vietnam" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, it is replaced by 
<taxonomicName id="7DE494AA9A79FFF23414F951A622F928" baseAuthorityName="Devyatkin" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[266,374,1714,1740]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubella">
<emphasis id="8890333B9A79FFF23414F951A622F928" box="[266,374,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">P. rubella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both species have not been found sympatrically so far. Although 
<taxonomicName id="7DE494AA9A79FFF23145F951A3BBF928" baseAuthorityName="Leech" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[1115,1263,1714,1740]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submacula">
<emphasis id="8890333B9A79FFF23145F951A3BBF928" box="[1115,1263,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">P. submacula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is separated by 
<taxonomicName id="7DE494AA9A79FFF23589F935A657F914" baseAuthorityName="Devyatkin" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[151,259,1750,1776]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubella">
<emphasis id="8890333B9A79FFF23589F935A657F914" box="[151,259,1750,1776]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">P. rubella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into two groups, specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="C2F3AFB99A79FFF23767F934A5E8F914" box="[633,700,1750,1776]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="C2F3AFB99A79FFF237EEF934A41BF914" box="[752,847,1750,1776]" name="Vietnam" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
are not distinguishable by stable external or genitalic characters. Therefore, the Vietnamese population of 
<taxonomicName id="7DE494AA9A79FFF237FCF919A422F8F0" baseAuthorityName="Leech" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[738,886,1786,1812]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submacula">
<emphasis id="8890333B9A79FFF237FCF919A422F8F0" box="[738,886,1786,1812]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">P. submacula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not considered a separate subspecies.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BA5BEF299A79FFF235D9F8FCA2C1F840" blockId="9.[151,1437,1570,1957]" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">
Geographical gaps between populations of species caused by natural factors are not rare in the butterfly fauna of Indochina. Disjunctions observed differ in their distance and direction. The majority of disjunctions in the Sino- Himalayan ranges has been observed between populations of northern 
<collectingCountry id="C2F3AFB99A79FFF236A5F884A34EF864" box="[955,1050,1894,1920]" name="Vietnam" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(e.g. Hoang Lien Son mountains) and northern part of central 
<collectingCountry id="C2F3AFB99A79FFF234CEF868A57BF840" box="[464,559,1930,1956]" name="Vietnam" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(northern Truong Son ridge), and populations of W. 
<collectingCountry id="C2F3AFB99A79FFF23163F868A394F840" box="[1149,1216,1930,1956]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="226">China</collectingCountry>
and E. Himalayas.
</paragraph>
